<br>
If anyone's curious, here's a bit on the stats (from a Monk's point of view though).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Statistics<br>
<br>
Each statistic will cap at 350. First there is your Power pool, which is used to cast spells and perform abilities. This pool is determined by 2 stats for each class. For the Monk, Stamina and Dexterity are utilized to determine your power pool.<br>
<br>
Strength<br>
<br>
Strength factors in to the maximum damage potential you have for each swing in melee combat. Direct Damage abilities will have a strength mod on them that will increase the damage the ability does based on the casters STR score.<br>
<br>
Dexterity<br>
<br>
Dexterity factors in to how much of your maximum damage potential you hit for each swing in melee combat. For ranged attacks Dexterity factors in to the maximum damage potential. Direct Damage spells will have a dexterity mod on them that will increase the damage the spell does based on the casters DEX.<br>
<br>
Agility <br>
<br>
Agility represents roughly 1/3 of your total defense.<br>
<br>
Stamina<br>
<br>
Stamina factors in to determining you Hit Points.<br>
<br>
Intelligence<br>
<br>
Intelligence factors in to calculating how likely you are to process &quot;Proc&quot; a spell when you have a buff on you that grants you a chance to proc. These spells have a base chance of 25% plus 1% for every 10 points of INT.<br>
<br>
Wisdom<br>
<br>
Wisdom factors in to how much of your maximum damage potential you hit for each shot/throw in ranged combat. Every 7 points of Wisdom adds 1 to all of your resistances.<br>
<br>
Charisma<br>
<br>
Charisma is used as a mod on heal spells. When casting heal spells you will heal a bonus amount that is determined by your CHA score. Spells that modify an NPCs behavior (Charm, Lull, Etc) will have a CHA mod on them that increases their duration.<br>
<br>
Starting Statistics<br>
<br>
STR STA AGI DEX WIS INT CHA <br>
Human 65 65 80 75 55 60 55&quot;<br>
<br>
Since its 500 years in the past, I can understand why Humans are weaker than they are in EQ.<br>
<br>
Monks start in Qeynos. The Ashen Order has not been established yet.<br>
<br>
It should be noted that the game has every class except beastlord.<br>
<br>
Every race except: <br>
<br>
Vah Shir (well no duh. They're up on the moon.) <br>
<br>
Ogres (weird, but I have a feeling they'll still be in the game, but just not as a playable race yet.) <br>
<br>
and <br>
<br>
IKSAR!!!! </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
