Sorcerer of The Hand, Xev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jakxev>JakXev</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.stny.rr.com/jazzmanian/weasel.jpe" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/21/02 11:48:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23139.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.stny.rr.com/jazzmanian/weasel.jpe WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Online Adventures?</span><hr size=1> Game mechanics and such (in terms of stats, class balancing, etc.) may be vastly improved in this game. Also, the graphics are staggeringly beautiful. Of course, this console was built with heavy graphics in mind, so that's no shock there.  And lag seems to not exist, and there's no &quot;zoning&quot; between zones. (Or so it seems.) So on some mechanical levels, it may indeed be the wave of the future.<br>
<br>
Now for the other side. Be prepared for a very different interactive experience. It's a lot quieter, and not in a good way. Until more changes are made (and they may be coming, have barely touched it since the switch from Alpha to Beta) conversation with your groupmates is insanely difficult. You still have to switch back and forth between the keyboard and that stupid PS2 controller. If you are in battle, with mobs coming in regularly, trying to type anything varies from tedious to life threatening. The &quot;canned&quot; chat responses you can pick using the controller are, of course, effectively useless.<br>
<br>
And there's still a lot of &quot;must have&quot; (IMO of course) features lacking. You can't autofollow, you can't /assist... just a bunch of things we take for granted that make life and combat in Norrath what we've come to know are not there.<br>
<br>
I mean, if you'd never played anything in your life except a PS game, then this may very well be heaven on Earth. But if you are used to PC based games in general, and the social atmosphere of EQ in particular, well...  I have to say, I'm hoping it evolved further, (and it may very well) but I just don't like it. Not because it's &quot;bad&quot;. But it *is* very different, and I guess I'm just too used to good old EQ on a computer.<br>
<br>
Re-reading this, I know it sounds like I'm dissing this game entirely. And I shouldn't. I think I'm just judging it based on the PC based game, when this really is a new game entirely, even if it does take place in a virtual world very much like ours in original EQ.<br>
<br>
Note: Some of the missing features may very well already be in the game and I just haven't figured them out yet. he he. <p>Jakiss, 57 Evoker of Xev<br> Souls of Honour <br> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243664">Jakiss' Wizzie Stuff</a><br><div align="center"> not allowed
